
  TV Display Procedures from Astronomical Users' Library   November, 1993
                   
    BLINK       :   To allow the user to alternatively examine two or more 
                    windows within a single window
    COMBINE_VEL :   Combine current color table with the velocity table of 
                    LOAD_VEL
    CURS        :   Change the shape of the X windows cursor
    CURVAL      :   Interactive display of image intensities and astronomical 
                    coordinates
    FORM_INT    :   Scale an intensity image into a byte array for use with 
                    COMBINE_VEL
    FORM_VEL    :   Scale a velocity image into a byte array for use with 
                    COMBINE_VEL
    LOAD_VEL    :   Load a color table to show velocities (blue - positive, 
                    red - negative)
    LOOKUP      :   Read and load color-tables from a database
    MODI_LUT    :   Program for interactive change of displaycolors in 
                    common block colors
    PIXCOLOR    :   Set specified pixel values to a specified color
    SIGRANGE    :   Find range of pixel values which contain 90% of the image 
                    values
    TVBOX       :   Draw a box of specified size on the image display
    TVCIRCLE    :   Draw a circle of specified radius on the image display
    TVELLIPSE   :   Draw an ellipse of specified axes on the image display
    TVLASER     :   Prints screen onto a Postscript laser printer
    TVLIST      :   Display intensity values surrounding the cursor position

